column4: Hmmm it seems that in one night the world changed a lot in the east part
It seems that the world changed a lot in the east part ...
it changed in the west, i know that much
no, he did not connect since several days
that is the west, isn't it?
that is the west, isn't it?
maluf duplicated some of my lines and is going broke
But I think that maluf and sephiroth are the same player ;)
19,84 the sawmill supplying this factory has not enough logs
two clients connected and the 2 companies were building
or maybe they know each other
both players will soon bankrupt and disappear anyway
if you like i can send logs to the sawmill or planks to the furniture factory
yes, Finn will eventually go too
Thanks ;) I don't want now to interfer with your network
i have excess lumber, it is no problem
but if i send too much your trucks will stop
just tell me what you want supplied to where
i built a goods line thru the city at 220,220, i hope it is ok with you
i tried not to interfere with your bus lines
i could have put it underground but i wanted to see it!
how long does it take to go bankrupt in multiplayer?
in solo you go bankrupt in 3 months of debt, but here you stay longer
if the city gets in your way, knock it down
too much passenger growth is a problem for you anyway...
But they'll go in bankrupt, be sure, the AI is already in it :)
i know they will, it happened to me with another pakset
the japan pak, i didn't realise it has no freight vehicles
Growth population is a good challenge :)
I build almost all rivers on the map to canals because sephiroth was beginnig to cut them at several points...
ha i know - been a while - hows it going?
g'day, so far so good, haven't gone broke once yet
ha well u did have some major jams - but they eased themself through
just in the past few hours?
u did have a major jam earlier - but it sorted itself out
it occurs once every so often
trains or trucks? do u remember where it was?
thought so - no one else calls gas stations servos :)
thought so - no one else calls gas stations servos :)
oh i like my stations to have short names
especially if they have to go through several destinations
ah, trains not such a problem as trucks, as they don't block anyone else
the word "servo" for petrol station is only used in australia afaik
btw u can delete ur signs at 47,179, et al.
i'll leave them there until tomorrow since maluf may not have come back
might help them figure out why they went broke
most of maluf's lines were copies of mine
i think it was high monthly costs: aka underground lines
no, hauling the same stuff between the same places
you're not going to make me forget that duplicating business are you :P lol
i don't think they looked underground
but he had several tunnels U/G
most of maluf's convoys never moved
waiting for stuff i was carrying
his duplication strategy wasn't as cunning as yours ;)
ha and mine was unintentional lol
im not used to a map with lots of underground :P so i have to look hard nowadays
i'm new to multiplayer, i guess it's an obvious temptation when you come in cold and see lots of stock sitting around
i don't normally do so much underground but i had to, to work around the passenger networks and the developed cities
actually the previous times i played this serious - ages ago - duplication was allowed if a certain industry wasnt full up
yeah i came in later than everyone else :P very hard to pick somewhere to start
that's another difference in multiplayer, growth occurs without you having to develop every city
duplication is allowed, no one can stop you
i mean i had a couple of my lines duplicated haha kinda started a war :P
this is a european game played mostly by europeans
in fact i had a played similar to maluf - so i bankrupted them :P
the european mindset is that there is room for everyone
once i came across a brazilian - who loved highways more than GAC [and airplanes!]
if this was an american game the whole idea would be to try to bankrupt each other
maybe we should have "european" and "american" rules
GAC built the highways to help new players
oh just depends on the players
yeah which is handy but i dont really use them :P
the problem for me if someone duplicates some lines of mine is that some of my convoys will stop
which can then stop everyone else
*face palm* i just realised the autobahns are right sided drive!
or even if someone was to take chemicals from a refinery that wasn't flat out
yeah, i had a laugh when i saw your motorway
you know that's a setting in the config file, yes?
which motorway of mine u referring to?
but of course with multiplayer clients don't choose that
and no i didnt know about that config setting
i wanted to try to use it to get to 484,259 but it's dedicated to the cotton farm there
oh, did you try to build ramps?
they are really hard to design when you're used to driving on the other side of the road
but it was only by chance when i saw a citycar whizz past
maybe we should stick to pak.britain ;)
ha ive never tried that pak :P
it's set to drive on the left, it's a very pretty pak too
the economics aren't good though, can be too easy or hard to make money
1st time i've used this pak, i really like it
yeah i migrated from pak64 last year- haventlooked back since
been using this pak for about a year [as in pak 128]
sorry if i lag or dc u - just buying about 30 trucks lol
no worries, i dc a lot anyway
i need lots of trucks as it's a pain to get a train to where ia m going - too many cities,highways, etc in the way
that's where underground comes in handy
ive yet to master the underground changing levels
hang on im just finishing off the last truck
the autobahn im using had 2 convois pass last month lol
whenever you want, either GAC or i can show u
how many will it have next month?

btw IF i finally found where u occasionally have jams

sorry, did not understand your question
cool, i know some brazilians, they are great people
